Oppenheimer Raises S&P 500 2011 Forecast, Cuts 2012 Predictions

-- B y   J o a n n a   O s s i n g e r
-- 
2011-10-10T14:20:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/oppenheimer-raises-s-p-500-2011-forecast-cuts-2012-predictions.html
Companies in the Standard & Poor’s
500 Index will earn $96 a share this year, Oppenheimer & Co.
said, raising its estimate from a previous $94.  The S&P 500 will end next year at 1,400, Oppenheimer’s
 Brian Belski  said in note on Oct. 7, cutting his forecast from a
prior 1,475. He said companies in the gauge will earn $101 a
share in 2012, down from a previous prediction of $112.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joanna Ossinger at 
 jossinger@bloomberg.net  